ldap.auth-mode.internal.desc.defaultMessage: Only local username/password authentication. LDAP is completely disabled.

ldap.auth-mode.internal-ldap.desc.defaultMessage: Users can log in with either local credentials or LDAP. Local auth is tried first, then LDAP as fallback.

ldap.auth-mode.ldap-only.desc.defaultMessage: Only LDAP authentication is allowed. Local passwords are ignored. Make sure at least one LDAP admin user exists!

ldap.connection-status.desc.defaultMessage: Live connection status to your LDAP server

ldap.user-sync.desc.defaultMessage: Manually sync all LDAP users into Better NPM. New users will be created, existing users will be updated.

ldap.connection-settings.desc.defaultMessage: Configure the connection to your LDAP server

ldap.host.help.defaultMessage: Hostname or IP address of the LDAP server. Leave empty if using a full URL below.

ldap.url.help.defaultMessage: Full LDAP URL. Use ldaps:// for SSL/TLS. Overrides host and port if set.

ldap.starttls.help.defaultMessage: Upgrade connection to TLS using STARTTLS extension

ldap.tls-verify.help.defaultMessage: Disable for self-signed certificates (not recommended for production)

ldap.multi-server.desc.defaultMessage: Add multiple LDAP servers for high availability. If configured, these override the single host/URL above. Servers are tried in priority order (lower number = higher priority).

ldap.bind-credentials.desc.defaultMessage: Service account used to search the LDAP directory. Leave empty for direct bind mode.

ldap.bind-dn.help.defaultMessage: Distinguished Name of the service account. For LLDAP: uid=admin,ou=people,dc=example,dc=com

ldap.search-settings.desc.defaultMessage: Configure how users are found in the LDAP directory

ldap.base-dn.help.defaultMessage: Base distinguished name for user search. For LLDAP: ou=people,dc=example,dc=com

ldap.user-dn-template.defaultMessage: User DN Template (for direct bind, optional)

ldap.user-dn-template.help.defaultMessage: Template for constructing the user DN directly. '{{USERNAME}}' will be replaced. Used when no service account is configured.

ldap.search-filter.help.defaultMessage: LDAP search filter. '{{USERNAME}}' is replaced with the login username. For Active Directory: (sAMAccountName='{{USERNAME}}'). For LLDAP: (|(uid='{{USERNAME}}')(mail='{{USERNAME}}'))

ldap.attribute-mapping.desc.defaultMessage: Map LDAP attributes to user fields

ldap.group-role-mapping.desc.defaultMessage: Optionally map LDAP groups to NPM admin role

ldap.admin-group.help.defaultMessage: Users in this LDAP group will be assigned the admin role. Leave empty to manage roles manually.

ldap.sync-admin-group.defaultMessage: Sync admin role on every login

ldap.sync-admin-group.help.defaultMessage: When enabled, the admin role is granted/revoked on each login based on LDAP group membership.

ldap.auto-create-user.help.defaultMessage: Automatically create a local user account when an LDAP user logs in for the first time.

ldap.sso.desc.defaultMessage: Enable Single Sign-On via trusted reverse proxy headers (e.g. Authelia, Authentik, Keycloak). When enabled, users authenticated by your reverse proxy are automatically logged in.

ldap.sso.enable.help.defaultMessage: When enabled, the login page will check for Remote-Email / Remote-User / Remote-Name headers set by your reverse proxy (e.g. Authelia) and automatically log users in. Users are auto-created if they don't exist. 2FA is skipped for SSO users.

ldap.sso.admin-emails.help.defaultMessage: Comma-separated list of email addresses that should always receive admin role via SSO. These users are promoted to admin on every SSO login, regardless of Remote-Groups.

ldap.sso.logout-url.help.defaultMessage: When a user logs out of NPM, they will be redirected to this URL to also end their SSO session (e.g. Authelia, Authentik, Keycloak logout endpoint).

ldap.sso.setup-desc.defaultMessage: Your reverse proxy must be configured to set the following headers when forwarding requests to NPM:

ldap.sso.header.groups.defaultMessage: Comma-separated groups (optional, used for admin role mapping)

ldap.timeouts.desc.defaultMessage: Connection and search timeout settings (in milliseconds)
